fields.description:
Currently, the "cargo-tarpaulin" app no longer works with the pipeline.

The user suggest adding "ADDR_NO_RANDOMIZE" in Docker seccomp profiles to get it working again:
{code}
{
  "names": [
    "personality"
  ],
  "action": "SCMP_ACT_ALLOW",
  "args": [
    {
      "index": 0,
      "value": 262144,
      "valueTwo": 0,
      "op": "SCMP_CMP_EQ"
    }
  ],
  "comment": "Enable personality(ADDR_NO_RANDOMIZE) syscall",
  "includes": {},
  "excludes": {}
}
{code}

Please review if it's possible to allow this in our current seccomp profiles.

Currently Bitbucket lacks highlighting when a destination branch from a pull request has changed.

If the New Pull Request Experience is active, the activity panel states there were changed to the commit (such as below), not to the PR/destination branch.
{panel}
UPDATED the pull request. The last commit was b589a93
{panel}
If the Old Pull Request Experience is active, the activity tab does not display any information related to this change.
